               <msContents>
                  <summary>
                     Sixth volume of an incomplete set of the <title>Rawz̤at al-Ṣafā</title> (Garden of Purity), a general history from the creation of the world to the time of the author, together
                     with <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6656"
                        ><idno>Persian MS 173</idno></ref>, <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_14609"
                           ><idno>174</idno></ref>, <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_14610">175</ref>, 
                     <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6657">176</ref>, and <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6659">178</ref>. However, the set lacks the fourth volume and a geographical appendix often added as the eighth, hence only six total. 
                     While nearly uniformly bound, the different formats and colophons within the set indicate completion in different location and times; however, this undated volume lacks a complete colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="manuscript_14610-item1">
                     <author key="person_175393012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/175393012/" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Mīr Khvānd, Muḥammad ibn Khāvandshāh, 1433-1498</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">مير خواند، محمد بن خواندشاه</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_273" change="#ids-cleanup">Rawz̤at al-Ṣafā fī Sīrat al-Anbiyā wa-al-Mulūk</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_273">Rawz̤at al-Ṣafā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_273" change="#ids-cleanup">روضة الصفاء فی سیرة الانبيا و الملوك</title>
                     <note>While this volume lacks an explicit colophon, a note on the <locus from="ia" to="ia">first right flyleaf (f. ia)</locus> bears an inspection notation written in <q xml:lang="fa"><hi rend="italic">dār al-Khilāfat Akbarābād</hi></q> (or the Mughal capital at <settlement type="city" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/153574610">Agra</settlement>) dated <q xml:lang="en">Thursday the 9th of the year 1006</q>, but curiously omits the month. 
                        Nevertheless, the day indicates possibly either the month of Jumādá I or Shavvāl of that year, hence the manuscript was completed before <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1598-05-15">15 May 1598</date>.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents> <physDesc>
